x4codes.hlp: On-line mass separation of a product

x4freetext: Separation of ions according to their A/q and
E/q values (with A, q, E - the mass,ionic charge state,
kinetic energy of the ions, respectively). Since
several nuclei can have the same A/q and E/q ratios,
an ionization chamber with two anodes is used to
further distinguish them.
Isotopic fission yields were determined by
gamma spectrometry. The beta-decay of the fission
products occurs after their flight path in the
spectrometer (about 1 micros). The fission products are
then implanted in a movable tape, the position of which
is fixed for each single gamma measurement (about 30
min).Two HPGe clover detectors are placed on each side
of the tape to measure the gamma-decay.
Ionization chamber measures the fragment energy
loss dE, deposited in the first part of the chamber,
as well as the total energy E deposited in the whole
chamber. Ionization chamber alone is used for the mass
yield measurement.
Setup with two HPGe clovers -  for the isotopic
yields determination.
Two different U3O8 targets for the mass yield
measurement : about one per week due to the target
burnup.
The first one was 68 microg/cm2 thick with an 233U
enrichment of 99.44 %, the second one 103 microg/cm2
thick with an 233U enrichment of 99.92 %.
Count rate of a mass was obtained independently from
its energy or charge.
For burnup - the "burnup" monitoring of the 233U target
was obtained by periodically measuring the kinetic
energy distribution of a given mass (136) at a fixed
ionic charge (21) and normalization to one at the
beginning of each measurement.

x4freetext: In symmetrical region authors measured from masses 105
to 113 in light peak, and from 120 to 127 in the heavy
peak. The measurements in the light region are
normalized on the heavy peak ones, and thus constitute
independent measurements, among which the masses 112,
113 and 114 never measured this way. The results for
heavy symmetrical region are not shown in this paper
though, since they still need to be thoroughly analyzed
Preliminary data.
Data are given on Fig.7,8 of C,2011GHENT,,(CINV21),2011
Only the productions of 52Te, 53I and 54Xe can be
estimated with our method, due to the long half-life of
55Cs - about 30 years. Since we could measure only part
of all the isotopes produced in the fission process, we
chose to normalize our results to the sum of the three
measured isotopes.By doing the same normalization on
the JEFF-3.1.1 library data, we can then get an
independent comparison of the isotopic productions for
these three isotopes.
E-gamma=243.3+-0.1 keV, intensity (71.6+-4.3) %.
Decay data from ENSDF .
